   OOuuttppuutt
       If the specified variable is defined on the system and its
       value is described to be available from the XSH specifica-
       tion  confstr  function,  its value will be written in the
       following format: "%s\n", <value>

       Otherwise, if the specified variable  is  defined  on  the
       system, its value will be written in the following format:
       "%d\n", <value>

       If the specified variable is valid, but  is  undefined  on
       the system, getconf will write using the following format:
       "undefined\n"

       If the variable name is invalid or an error occurs,  noth-
       ing will be written to standard output.

